headline: Analyst explains why coffee prices are rising in 2025
summary: Investing.com -- Coffee prices soared nearly 60% over the last six months, with the price of Arabica beans reaching a 50-year peak, stirring concerns about the potential impact on the margins of coffee chains like Starbucks (NASDAQ:SBUX) and Tim Hortons (NYSE:QSR), as well as the resilience of consumer demand.

headline: 3 Reasons to Buy Dutch Bros Stock Like There's No Tomorrow
summary: Shares of Dutch Bros (NYSE: BROS) have fallen 25% or so from their February 2025 highs.  It just sells coffee, competing against brands like Dunkin' and Starbucks (NASDAQ: SBUX).  In other words, Dutch Bros isn't playing on some faddish food concept, hoping to gain enough traction to create a lasting business.
